100 μL of the Baicalin capsule solution was added into 200 μL of N-CDs solution, followed by adding distilled water to the volume of 3 mL and shaking well. The fluorescence intensity Fx was measured, and then the Baicalin content was calculated by standard curve method. The Baicalin content was measured using the HPLC analysis as a contrast method described in Pharmacopoeia (Fig. 7
                           ). According to t-test, the results obtained by the two methods were not significant difference (t = 1.74, df = 5, p = 2.57, Table2
                           ).
